quran[6]{c,v,t}:
  5,77,"Say, “O People of the Book! Do not go to extremes in your faith beyond the truth, nor follow the vain desires of those who went astray before ˹you˺. They misled many and strayed from the Right Way.”"
  5,78,"The disbelievers among the Children of Israel were condemned in the revelations of David and Jesus, son of Mary. That was for their disobedience and violations"
  5,79,They did not forbid one another from doing evil. Evil indeed was what they did
  5,80,"You see many of them taking the disbelievers as allies. Truly wicked are their misdeeds, which have earned them God’s wrath. And they will be in everlasting torment"
  5,81,"Had they believed in God, the Prophet, and what has been revealed to him, they would have never taken those ˹pagans˺ as allies. But most of them are rebellious"
  5,82,You will surely find the most bitter towards the believers to be the Jews and polytheists and the most gracious to be those who call themselves Christian. That is because there are priests and monks among them and because they are not arrogant